                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15 Arms Truce/47: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-27T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >September 27, 1931—8 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 27—4:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>169. Supplementing my 168, September 27, 11 a.m. Conversations later today have
                    revealed that French text may permit France to continue naval construction under
                    its 5–year building program while other states would undertake to abstain from
                    “new initiative”. Grandi now flatly refuses French text. There will probably,
                    therefore, be no unanimous agreement tomorrow other than Scandinavian
                    resolution.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
